\[\lfloor y \rfloor \le 0,\]so $0 \le y < 1.$

For $0.01 \le x < 0.02,$ we want
\[\lfloor y \rfloor \le 1,\]so $0 \le y < 2.$

For $0.02 \le x < 0.03,$ we want
\[\lfloor y \rfloor \le 2,\]so $0 \le y < 3,$ and so on.

