Putting the distance per time into the formula, we have $$d = 1,320,000 \text{ feet/hour}\cdot t = 20,000 \text{ feet}$$ Solving for t, we get $$t = \dfrac{20,000}{1,320,000}$$ so the time it takes for the plane to go 20,000 feet is $$t = \dfrac{20,000}{1,320,000} \text{ hours}$$
